          h2 It all started with a tiger
          p I started by looking at stock photos on shutterstock to find a direction I wanted to take the designs in. I was going through themes that I felt were appropriate for us a couple. But the standard “wedding” themed illustrations were not cutting it. Meagan and I are not your standard default picture frame couple. So I found an illustration of a tiger dressed like a human. It was love at first site.
          img(src="/img/work/wedding-collateral/wedding-collateral-tiger-01.jpg")
          h2 Save the date
          p For the save the dates I wanted something that people will not only want to put on their fridge. I wanted people to keep it on their fridge way after the wedding. Most of the examples I had seen had pictures of the couple. We didn’t include photos because the people who we invite should know it’s us by our names being on the print. If they don’t know they shouldn’t show up to our wedding. Because we knew our audience. We made two versions of the card. One for our friends and the other with a more conservative headline for the family. I knew the tiger illustration would cause intrigue and let people know this ain't their mother's wedding. The card got the reaction I was looking for. That is people were pumped about the event.
      section.col-3-3
